My husband and I are vegan and was interested in getting veggie sliders that were on the menu. The waiter took our order then after another half hour wait, told us they were out of veggie sliders. We ended up ordering 2 orders of fries. After another 15 minute wait the waiter brought out one order of fries and forgot the other.  I decided to continue to support my people so I gave this place another chance. I came here on a Sunday. It was not crowded. We did not get greeted at the door and we did not get seated. We decided to take it upon ourselves to sit at the bar. The waitress came over and tossed 2 menus towards us. We asked if there were any available tables, she said no. We looked at lunch menu and this time there were no vegetarian options on it. We asked if we could tweek something from the menu to add vegetables and the waitress seemed as if we were giving her too much of a task. There was a lot of attitude and she seemed frustrated. I understand this is a new business but it’s unfair to people who are coming to support and just looking for a bite to eat. I wish this business much luck as success and I hope things get better for them.
